WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

00:00:04.638 --> 00:00:06.106
It's finally about to begin.

00:00:06.874 --> 00:00:08.175
We're here

00:00:09.409 --> 00:00:10.844
in Tokyo.

00:00:11.245 --> 00:00:13.714
This will be your dream stage, NAZE!

00:00:18.018 --> 00:00:20.387
Excuse me, whose house is this?

00:00:20.487 --> 00:00:25.559
Surprise! This is the home
of the genius producer, Mr. Azuma

00:00:25.626 --> 00:00:28.028
and you're going to live with him!

00:00:31.198 --> 00:00:33.600
Why my home? I don't like this.

00:00:33.667 --> 00:00:34.668
Shut up.

00:00:34.768 --> 00:00:37.371
If you're unhappy,
complain to that traitorous woman.

00:00:37.437 --> 00:00:39.206
Ouch... I can't breathe...

00:00:40.007 --> 00:00:41.909
Everything failed.

00:00:42.009 --> 00:00:45.078
No Korean media, including TV,
the internet, and magazines

00:00:45.145 --> 00:00:46.847
is willing to cover NAZE.

00:00:47.481 --> 00:00:49.383
They're leftovers, after all.

00:00:50.017 --> 00:00:52.786
- Hey!
- That woman, Park Ji-soo

00:00:52.886 --> 00:00:55.355
is definitely pulling strings
behind the scenes

00:00:55.455 --> 00:00:58.025
by using her agency's
money and influence.

00:00:59.326 --> 00:01:01.128
You darn coward!

00:01:09.102 --> 00:01:10.537
Now that it's come to this

00:01:11.838 --> 00:01:12.839
I'll have to use my ace in the hole.

00:01:13.340 --> 00:01:14.341
Ace in the hole?

00:01:15.208 --> 00:01:16.243
I'll bet...

00:01:17.511 --> 00:01:19.546
on the potential
of the Japanese market!

00:01:19.646 --> 00:01:21.248
My house has nothing to do with that!

00:01:21.315 --> 00:01:22.950
Why not? You have a house in Tokyo.

00:01:23.016 --> 00:01:25.552
- Let us use it for a while.
- Stingy!

00:01:26.520 --> 00:01:27.521
Okay!

00:01:28.088 --> 00:01:30.157
This is the beginning of
a dreamy life of

00:01:30.257 --> 00:01:31.391
being surrounded by hot guys!

00:01:31.658 --> 00:01:34.061
A genius producer lives in
a house like this?

00:01:34.628 --> 00:01:36.296
Is it haunted?

00:01:36.363 --> 00:01:37.598
Shut up.

00:01:37.798 --> 00:01:39.900
It's called rustic charm in Japan.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:43.437
It looks more run-down than rustic.

00:01:43.503 --> 00:01:44.638
That was pretty witty, you fool.

00:01:44.705 --> 00:01:46.473
Listen.

00:01:46.573 --> 00:01:48.208
I'm letting you stay for free.

00:01:48.275 --> 00:01:50.243
If you don't like it,
go back to Korea. Your answer?

00:01:51.345 --> 00:01:52.746
- Understood.
- Understood.

00:01:52.813 --> 00:01:55.248
Leave your stuff here.
We'll start practicing right away.

00:01:55.315 --> 00:01:56.350
- Okay.
- Okay.

00:01:56.950 --> 00:01:59.720
- Thanks for having me!
- It's low! Like my grandma's home!

00:01:59.786 --> 00:02:02.489
Thank you, Mr. Azuma.

00:02:02.589 --> 00:02:03.790
What?

00:02:04.291 --> 00:02:07.761
The relationship between Kun
and his mom improved because of you

00:02:08.228 --> 00:02:10.731
and now you're even letting them
stay at your house.

00:02:11.264 --> 00:02:13.834
I'll help you as much as I can.

00:02:13.934 --> 00:02:16.370
- No need.
- Yes! I'll do my utmost...

00:02:17.904 --> 00:02:19.606
I don't need you.

00:02:19.706 --> 00:02:22.743
It's faster to do everything myself
than to have you get in the way.

00:02:23.877 --> 00:02:25.646
Even so, I want to help the boys--

00:02:25.712 --> 00:02:27.347
How long are you going
to make me wait?

00:02:27.447 --> 00:02:29.316
Let's hurry to the practice studio!

00:02:30.817 --> 00:02:32.953
Apparently, NAZE ran away to Japan.

00:02:34.154 --> 00:02:35.489
What? I don't think they ran away.

00:02:35.555 --> 00:02:37.691
They're K-pop idols,
but they want to work in Japan.

00:02:37.791 --> 00:02:38.892
Isn't that ridiculous?

00:02:39.326 --> 00:02:42.396
But I get why they ran away.
People compare us to them.

00:02:44.398 --> 00:02:47.134
A hundred jumping burpees
and a hundred push-ups!

00:02:47.734 --> 00:02:51.104
What, exhausted already?
You have no time to feel tired!

00:02:53.173 --> 00:02:54.708
Oh, no...

00:02:54.808 --> 00:02:57.577
The water in the pantry won't
turn off! Do something!

00:02:57.644 --> 00:03:00.247
- Turn off the water yourself!
- I can't!

00:03:00.847 --> 00:03:02.282
Why are you always doing this
when I'm busy...

00:03:02.349 --> 00:03:04.117
Guys, don't slack off!

00:03:04.618 --> 00:03:06.687
Ouch! It hurts!

00:03:09.022 --> 00:03:10.390
She's our lifesaver!

00:03:10.457 --> 00:03:12.693
This is too intense
right off the bat!

00:03:15.696 --> 00:03:18.532
Mr. Azuma told you not to slack off.

00:03:18.598 --> 00:03:19.900
- You don't need a phone--
- What?

00:03:19.966 --> 00:03:21.968
- Seriously?
- What happened?

00:03:22.369 --> 00:03:24.137
TORINNER is appearing
at a live event!

00:03:24.237 --> 00:03:25.439
- What?
- What?

00:03:25.505 --> 00:03:26.907
TORINNER makes history

00:03:27.007 --> 00:03:28.408
as the first group
to take the stage at K-FLARE

00:03:28.475 --> 00:03:30.210
less than a year after their debut.

00:03:30.277 --> 00:03:33.246
K-FLARE is a huge K-pop event, right?

00:03:33.947 --> 00:03:36.349
Yeah, rookies normally
aren't allowed to participate.

00:03:36.416 --> 00:03:39.019
Big agencies sure have leverage!

00:03:39.086 --> 00:03:41.988
I want to shine brightly
like them, too!

00:03:42.089 --> 00:03:44.057
Ryo is charismatic
and has good looks.

00:03:44.157 --> 00:03:45.225
He naturally draws in fans...

00:03:45.325 --> 00:03:47.661
You're so different
from your brother.

00:03:49.129 --> 00:03:50.263
It doesn't matter.

00:03:52.165 --> 00:03:53.533
TOKYO GIRLS COLLECTION TO BE HELD!

00:03:53.600 --> 00:03:55.669
What? Is this an event in Japan?

00:03:56.103 --> 00:03:57.370
So cool!

00:03:57.471 --> 00:03:59.072
TGC is very famous.

00:03:59.172 --> 00:04:01.308
Now that we're back in Japan

00:04:01.374 --> 00:04:03.043
I want to perform
on a big stage like this.

00:04:03.110 --> 00:04:05.712
You dream too big. It's impossible.

00:04:07.414 --> 00:04:08.415
I'm sure you--

00:04:08.482 --> 00:04:10.650
We'll make our dreams come true!

00:04:10.751 --> 00:04:12.886
Let's go to TGC!

00:04:13.487 --> 00:04:15.288
Our house and studio are so shabby.

00:04:15.388 --> 00:04:16.690
How can we have dreams?

00:04:18.425 --> 00:04:22.129
True. At this rate,
I doubt we can even debut.

00:04:24.064 --> 00:04:26.500
That's why you have to practice--

00:04:28.368 --> 00:04:29.436
It's hopeless.

00:04:29.903 --> 00:04:33.373
What are you doing?
I told you not to slack off!

00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:36.409
If you don't have the motivation,
I'll disband the group immediately!

00:04:36.510 --> 00:04:37.844
- Yes!
- Sorry!

00:04:37.911 --> 00:04:40.714
Sorry. I know I was supposed
to supervise them.

00:04:40.781 --> 00:04:42.182
I did try to warn them--

00:04:42.282 --> 00:04:44.684
Didn't you say
you were going to give it your all?

00:04:44.785 --> 00:04:47.387
I guess it's only
as much as an ant can do.

00:04:49.022 --> 00:04:50.557
Hey, where are the towels?

00:04:53.126 --> 00:04:54.361
An ant?

00:05:04.404 --> 00:05:07.507
That manager is so useless, though.

00:05:07.574 --> 00:05:09.009
It's Endo Minase.

00:05:09.709 --> 00:05:14.314
Minase didn't plan
on working in showbiz at first.

00:05:14.381 --> 00:05:17.150
- Is that so?
- When she was in high school

00:05:17.884 --> 00:05:21.188
that poor girl was bullied
and had a tough time.

00:05:21.788 --> 00:05:23.623
That's why she left Japan after that

00:05:23.824 --> 00:05:25.458
and entered
Seoul National University.

00:05:25.892 --> 00:05:28.829
Seoul National University, hear that?
She's extremely outstanding!

00:05:29.930 --> 00:05:31.698
She's good at studying

00:05:32.265 --> 00:05:34.301
but she doesn't seem
to have confidence in herself.

00:05:34.401 --> 00:05:37.103
Her job hunting
didn't go well either.

00:05:37.170 --> 00:05:38.939
So you deceived the poor girl

00:05:39.005 --> 00:05:41.575
and lured her
into this cash-strapped agency?

00:05:41.641 --> 00:05:43.009
Watch your mouth!

00:05:43.276 --> 00:05:44.444
Mr. Azuma.

00:05:44.544 --> 00:05:45.779
You again?

00:05:45.846 --> 00:05:47.280
My name is Endo Minase.

00:05:47.380 --> 00:05:48.949
I'd like to tell you something--

00:05:49.049 --> 00:05:50.684
I won't listen.

00:05:52.519 --> 00:05:54.354
This is TORINNER,
a group that trained with NAZE.

00:05:54.421 --> 00:05:56.656
They will be performing
in a big event in Korea.

00:05:56.723 --> 00:05:58.458
The boys all got upset
when they found out.

00:05:58.558 --> 00:06:01.127
There it is! A major agency's
money and influence!

00:06:01.228 --> 00:06:04.831
I want to do everything I can
for the boys.

00:06:05.732 --> 00:06:07.701
Is there anything I can--

00:06:07.801 --> 00:06:09.269
No.

00:06:09.402 --> 00:06:11.972
They never listen to you anyway.

00:06:12.639 --> 00:06:14.541
Then, at least have a look at this.

00:06:15.508 --> 00:06:17.544
This is a compilation of

00:06:17.644 --> 00:06:20.981
all the ideas I had
on how to promote them.

00:06:21.081 --> 00:06:23.350
I've been thinking about it
for a while.

00:06:23.450 --> 00:06:26.186
Wow! When did you do this?

00:06:27.020 --> 00:06:29.923
And this is
a record of their daily lives.

00:06:30.023 --> 00:06:32.125
Once you get to know
their wonderful individualities

00:06:32.192 --> 00:06:33.460
you can use that to produce--

00:06:33.560 --> 00:06:35.128
Not necessary.

00:06:36.129 --> 00:06:38.732
I don't like
people telling me what to do.

00:06:39.499 --> 00:06:43.336
Besides, you've been coming up with
ideas to promote them for a while?

00:06:44.571 --> 00:06:46.773
In that case, why haven't you
put them into action?

00:06:48.375 --> 00:06:49.376
That's because...

00:06:49.476 --> 00:06:52.679
You didn't have the resolve
to take responsibility yourself

00:06:52.746 --> 00:06:55.015
so you wanted to rely on me.
Am I right?

00:06:55.715 --> 00:06:57.651
You don't want to fail and get hurt.

00:07:00.053 --> 00:07:03.223
Producing artists isn't
a simulation game.

00:07:04.824 --> 00:07:07.394
If you aren't prepared
to be responsible for their lives

00:07:08.161 --> 00:07:09.429
our team doesn't need you.

00:07:12.632 --> 00:07:14.267
You are right.

00:07:15.669 --> 00:07:16.670
But...

00:07:17.270 --> 00:07:19.706
Even so, I want
to find somethingI can do.

00:07:21.741 --> 00:07:25.378
If I carry on like this,
I'll have nothing.

00:07:25.478 --> 00:07:28.481
Minase, it's okay.
Don't be so hard on yourself.

00:07:28.548 --> 00:07:30.350
- You're helpful--
- You'll have nothing?

00:07:35.121 --> 00:07:37.157
I've never had confidence in myself.

00:07:38.725 --> 00:07:41.761
I could only do
what others told me. But...

00:07:41.861 --> 00:07:43.596
You want to change your useless self

00:07:43.663 --> 00:07:46.199
so you plan to stake their futures
on a gamble?

00:07:46.266 --> 00:07:47.400
How arrogant!

00:07:49.836 --> 00:07:51.638
NAZE PROMOTION MATERIALS

00:07:57.077 --> 00:07:58.211
How can you be so mean?

00:07:58.311 --> 00:08:00.046
You didn't have to go that far!

00:08:00.113 --> 00:08:03.616
It's crueler to keep her tied
to a job she's not suited for.

00:08:03.683 --> 00:08:06.786
How do you know
what would make Minase happy?

00:08:07.387 --> 00:08:10.123
Do you have the right
to belittle her life?

00:08:10.557 --> 00:08:12.392
Are you going to abandon us now?

00:08:12.492 --> 00:08:14.961
Are you okay with ruining our lives?

00:08:19.566 --> 00:08:20.934
Oh, sorry.

00:08:22.068 --> 00:08:23.303
You know

00:08:23.903 --> 00:08:26.272
she sometimes
has trouble communicating

00:08:26.339 --> 00:08:28.108
but she's trying really hard.

00:08:30.610 --> 00:08:32.979
See? Look at this!

00:08:33.079 --> 00:08:36.516
Not many people can be
as detailed as her!

00:08:37.450 --> 00:08:38.451
This is for Younki.

00:08:39.586 --> 00:08:40.720
Wait, for all of them?

00:08:42.088 --> 00:08:44.557
An honest person
who truly loves idols

00:08:44.924 --> 00:08:47.794
is more suited to be a manager
than a competent liar.

00:08:48.395 --> 00:08:51.197
Yeah, you can
almost call her a stalker.

00:08:51.264 --> 00:08:52.866
It's love. Love!

00:09:05.412 --> 00:09:06.479
In any case

00:09:07.080 --> 00:09:10.417
since the boys are feeling anxious,
we should do something for them.

00:09:11.284 --> 00:09:13.420
Tell them about your plans for them!

00:09:13.520 --> 00:09:15.355
Plans, you say?

00:09:15.955 --> 00:09:17.991
I need to reconsider
my life plan first and think about

00:09:18.058 --> 00:09:21.194
whether I should continue staying
with this poor agency.

00:09:21.461 --> 00:09:23.797
"A career change in my thirties."

00:09:24.998 --> 00:09:27.100
You owe me money!

00:09:27.167 --> 00:09:28.234
Ten million!

00:09:36.543 --> 00:09:37.544
I know.

00:09:38.845 --> 00:09:41.114
I know I have to change.

00:09:41.581 --> 00:09:44.284
You need to make a complete change!

00:09:44.384 --> 00:09:46.553
In just an hour since you got here

00:09:46.619 --> 00:09:48.788
my house has turned
into a complete mess!

00:09:49.055 --> 00:09:53.093
Dirty! Sloppy!
Stop depending on others!

00:09:53.193 --> 00:09:54.561
- Yes, I'm sorry.
- Yes, I'm sorry.

00:09:54.627 --> 00:09:56.529
Sit down to use the toilet.

00:09:56.629 --> 00:09:58.331
Vacuum every morning.

00:09:58.398 --> 00:10:00.867
Get wrinkles out of your clothes
before hanging them.

00:10:00.934 --> 00:10:02.836
Rotate cooking duties...

00:10:02.902 --> 00:10:03.903
So fussy.

00:10:03.970 --> 00:10:04.971
Don't let food expire.

00:10:05.038 --> 00:10:06.039
I can't remember all of that.

00:10:06.306 --> 00:10:07.907
- Let's dig in!
- Let's dig in!

00:10:09.676 --> 00:10:11.144
- So good!
- Delicious!

00:10:12.145 --> 00:10:13.947
Wait. Only bean sprouts
and pea shoots?

00:10:14.047 --> 00:10:15.982
I can't find any meat.

00:10:16.082 --> 00:10:17.117
Due to a tight budget
in this household

00:10:17.183 --> 00:10:19.252
only people with pure hearts
can see meat here.

00:10:19.319 --> 00:10:20.320
Look, I found it.

00:10:20.420 --> 00:10:21.721
- What?
- What?

00:10:21.788 --> 00:10:23.389
Rock, paper, scissors!

00:10:23.490 --> 00:10:25.258
- Yes!
- Yes!

00:10:25.325 --> 00:10:27.360
What are you doing? Go to bed now.

00:10:27.961 --> 00:10:29.863
- Good night.
- Good night.

00:10:30.830 --> 00:10:33.199
Please, anywhere but
next to Mr. Azuma.

00:10:33.299 --> 00:10:37.036
Praying for a good harvest, fortune,
prosperity, health, and peace.

00:10:38.071 --> 00:10:40.940
Rock, paper, scissors!

00:10:43.009 --> 00:10:44.878
- Good night.
- Good night.

00:10:46.513 --> 00:10:47.981
Good morning.

00:10:48.414 --> 00:10:50.049
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

00:10:50.150 --> 00:10:52.218
Excuse me, where is Mr. Azuma?

00:10:52.652 --> 00:10:53.653
Hey.

00:10:53.987 --> 00:10:55.555
I have a meeting outside today,
so I won't be going to the office.

00:10:55.655 --> 00:10:57.190
Why are you wearing a suit?

00:10:57.290 --> 00:10:58.892
Guys, do basic training
after stretching.

00:10:59.292 --> 00:11:01.728
A three-minute plank and 100 squats.

00:11:01.794 --> 00:11:03.663
You'll have two hours
of singing lessons after that.

00:11:04.230 --> 00:11:05.798
You have language
and acting classes in the afternoon

00:11:05.899 --> 00:11:09.235
and your dance coach will come
in the evening, so... Right!

00:11:09.302 --> 00:11:10.904
You have modeling classes, too.

00:11:10.970 --> 00:11:12.438
Record their training on video.
Don't let them slack off.

00:11:12.772 --> 00:11:14.641
- I'll check it later.
- Yes.

00:11:14.707 --> 00:11:15.775
And also...

00:11:17.110 --> 00:11:19.312
Don't forget
the rules I told you yesterday.

00:11:19.979 --> 00:11:21.347
- Yes.
- Yes.

00:11:21.414 --> 00:11:23.416
What rules?

00:11:24.384 --> 00:11:25.785
What are they?

00:11:25.852 --> 00:11:28.621
There are a lot of rules
for freeloaders.

00:11:28.688 --> 00:11:31.124
But we've been working on
our fundamentals the entire time!

00:11:32.125 --> 00:11:34.460
The gap between TORINNER and us
is growing.

00:11:42.502 --> 00:11:45.171
Mr. Azuma, I'd like
to say something--

00:11:45.238 --> 00:11:46.606
Sorry, I'm in a hurry.

00:11:49.542 --> 00:11:50.543
I'm also...

00:11:52.178 --> 00:11:54.814
prepared to take responsibility
for the boys and their lives.

00:11:58.851 --> 00:12:00.653
If there's anything I can do

00:12:01.487 --> 00:12:02.689
I want to help them.

00:12:06.559 --> 00:12:07.994
Some of them are worried that

00:12:08.061 --> 00:12:09.729
just working on the fundamentals
isn't enough.

00:12:10.296 --> 00:12:12.465
So I want to ease
their anxiety a bit.

00:12:13.066 --> 00:12:15.868
Isn't there something
we can set as a goal?

00:12:18.605 --> 00:12:19.606
A live performance.

00:12:20.306 --> 00:12:22.742
- Live performance?
- That has to be their goal.

00:12:22.976 --> 00:12:25.178
I want them to have the courage
to perform in front of an audience.

00:12:25.979 --> 00:12:28.381
Really? They will be thrilled.

00:12:28.448 --> 00:12:29.682
- In that case, I'll leave it to you.
- What?

00:12:29.782 --> 00:12:33.086
Look for an event or a festival
for them to perform at.

00:12:33.186 --> 00:12:35.088
How am I supposed to do that?

00:12:35.154 --> 00:12:36.589
You said you were prepared, remember?

00:12:50.303 --> 00:12:52.171
LIST OF EVENTS IN TOKYO

00:12:54.140 --> 00:12:55.141
Okay!

00:12:55.508 --> 00:12:57.644
NAZE? Never heard of them.

00:12:57.744 --> 00:12:59.612
The boys are very passionate.

00:12:59.712 --> 00:13:00.947
So they're amateurs.

00:13:01.047 --> 00:13:03.816
Yes, but they're training hard
right now.

00:13:03.916 --> 00:13:06.552
You can't expect me to trust you
when you show up out of the blue.

00:13:06.619 --> 00:13:09.355
Sorry, but if you could
just hear me out...

00:13:10.356 --> 00:13:11.724
The venue is this way.

00:13:11.824 --> 00:13:13.393
Please watch your step.

00:13:14.127 --> 00:13:15.595
Let's get to work.

00:13:15.695 --> 00:13:17.330
The venue is this way.

00:13:19.666 --> 00:13:22.535
Your arms aren't aligned!
Your balance is off, too.

00:13:22.635 --> 00:13:25.271
Wanderlust is the only song you have.

00:13:25.338 --> 00:13:27.974
No one will even look at you
if you're so bad!

00:13:34.013 --> 00:13:35.948
Seriously, you can't even
do crab steps?

00:13:36.015 --> 00:13:37.317
You're already out of breath.

00:13:37.383 --> 00:13:39.319
You lack stamina,
and you're so bad at dancing.

00:13:39.519 --> 00:13:40.520
I'm sorry.

00:13:40.620 --> 00:13:43.089
Your brother, Ryo, is a fast learner
and outstanding.

00:13:43.189 --> 00:13:45.358
You're so different from him.

00:13:46.626 --> 00:13:47.760
Okay, once more!

00:13:48.728 --> 00:13:49.729
- Yes.
- Yes.

00:14:00.807 --> 00:14:03.476
LIST OF EVENTS IN TOKYO

00:14:04.010 --> 00:14:05.244
There are still many more to go.

00:14:12.251 --> 00:14:14.620
Is he actually reading
at a time like this?

00:14:15.588 --> 00:14:17.857
Are we still not there yet?

00:14:17.924 --> 00:14:19.359
We're not interested in rookies.

00:14:19.459 --> 00:14:21.861
But I'd consider it if it's TORINNER.

00:14:21.928 --> 00:14:23.429
After all, they are
the talk of the town.

00:14:23.496 --> 00:14:26.899
You're getting in the way!
Can't you tell I'm busy?

00:14:26.999 --> 00:14:28.501
I am sorry!

00:14:28.568 --> 00:14:29.802
Sixty.

00:14:31.537 --> 00:14:32.572
Sixty-one.

00:14:33.673 --> 00:14:35.942
So, what do I stand to gain
from this?

00:14:40.446 --> 00:14:43.449
Five, six, seven, eight...

00:14:44.851 --> 00:14:46.786
Five, six, seven, eight.

00:14:46.886 --> 00:14:49.789
One, two, three, four, five, six...

00:14:50.390 --> 00:14:54.093
Yuya! Wrong, wrong, wrong!
Why can't you do it?

00:14:54.160 --> 00:14:55.428
I'm sorry.

00:14:56.529 --> 00:14:57.997
One more time, please.

00:14:58.064 --> 00:14:59.098
Once more!

00:14:59.165 --> 00:15:01.701
Five, six, seven, eight. One...

00:15:03.469 --> 00:15:05.438
Five, six, seven, eight.

00:15:05.505 --> 00:15:10.243
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

00:15:10.343 --> 00:15:12.078
LIST OF EVENTS IN TOKYO

00:15:14.013 --> 00:15:16.416
Have you found an event?

00:15:17.750 --> 00:15:19.085
I'm doing my best.

00:15:20.286 --> 00:15:21.687
Your best again?

00:15:22.522 --> 00:15:24.424
Do you even know what that means?

00:15:25.057 --> 00:15:26.058
Of course.

00:15:26.159 --> 00:15:28.628
I give it my all
to do my best every day--

00:15:28.694 --> 00:15:31.864
So, it's still
at the level of an ant.

00:15:34.367 --> 00:15:37.303
Yes, I may be an ant.

00:15:40.606 --> 00:15:42.074
But I will find one.

00:15:46.979 --> 00:15:48.080
Do your best.

00:15:55.455 --> 00:15:58.391
Lead music

00:16:01.060 --> 00:16:02.395
Aragaki Reina

00:16:07.033 --> 00:16:08.367
DREAM SUPER LIVE TO BE HELD

00:16:08.434 --> 00:16:10.002
MANY FAMOUS ARTISTS WILL BE FEATURED

00:16:19.278 --> 00:16:20.880
There aren't many left.

00:16:24.183 --> 00:16:25.918
Wow, this is so good!

00:16:26.419 --> 00:16:29.322
Hey, give me a bite.

00:16:29.388 --> 00:16:30.790
Why? Eat your own.

00:16:30.890 --> 00:16:32.625
- I want to try them all!
- What are they doing

00:16:32.692 --> 00:16:34.760
at a time like this?

00:16:36.229 --> 00:16:38.197
You still can't do it, Yuya?

00:16:38.264 --> 00:16:41.200
You keep repeating the same mistake.
Are you sure you want this?

00:16:41.801 --> 00:16:42.802
I'm sorry.

00:16:43.202 --> 00:16:46.372
Are you really the younger brother
of TORINNER's Ryo?

00:16:47.773 --> 00:16:51.777
Your looks, talent, and stamina
all pale in comparison to Ryo's.

00:16:54.614 --> 00:16:55.781
Once more!

00:16:56.382 --> 00:16:59.552
Here we go! Five, six, seven, eight.

00:16:59.619 --> 00:17:00.720
One, two...

00:17:01.754 --> 00:17:04.290
The poster for K-FLARE,
the event I mentioned, has arrived.

00:17:04.790 --> 00:17:06.325
- Wow...
- Amazing.

00:17:06.425 --> 00:17:08.694
It's one of the greatest K-pop events
in Korea.

00:17:09.295 --> 00:17:10.897
Don't let me down.

00:17:10.963 --> 00:17:12.331
- Understood!
- Understood!

00:17:17.570 --> 00:17:19.138
Only Ryo stands out.

00:17:19.205 --> 00:17:21.340
Even just a short while will do.

00:17:21.874 --> 00:17:25.411
Will you let them perform
at this festival?

00:17:26.212 --> 00:17:28.147
I know how you feel

00:17:28.247 --> 00:17:31.083
but what can they actually do?

00:17:31.150 --> 00:17:34.921
They practice singing and dancing
for 14 hours every day.

00:17:35.521 --> 00:17:37.490
Diligently, with everything
they've got.

00:17:37.557 --> 00:17:39.692
That's a given if they're aiming
to be professional idols.

00:17:40.326 --> 00:17:43.195
I'm talking about their unique charm.

00:17:46.432 --> 00:17:47.700
Unique...

00:17:51.037 --> 00:17:52.572
If you don't even know that

00:17:53.239 --> 00:17:56.709
then why should I support this group?

00:17:57.443 --> 00:18:01.280
Don't you know being diligent
and hardworking alone isn't enough?

00:18:02.315 --> 00:18:05.418
If that's the case, perhaps you're
not suited for this job.

00:18:08.854 --> 00:18:10.323
I'm not suited for this job?

00:18:10.957 --> 00:18:12.758
Of course I know that.

00:18:22.268 --> 00:18:24.503
Their unique charm...

00:18:27.206 --> 00:18:30.276
I can't even figure out
something so important.

00:18:38.651 --> 00:18:40.820
RESIGNATION LETTER

00:18:53.299 --> 00:18:54.567
Yuya?

00:18:58.270 --> 00:18:59.372
Minase...

00:19:02.008 --> 00:19:03.009
Welcome back.

00:19:04.176 --> 00:19:07.913
What's the matter?
Shouldn't you be having dinner now?

00:19:09.448 --> 00:19:11.584
Yes, but...

00:19:12.251 --> 00:19:14.754
I've been causing trouble
for everyone.

00:19:14.854 --> 00:19:17.657
So I wanted
to build up my stamina first.

00:19:18.557 --> 00:19:20.559
So you've been jogging alone?

00:19:21.193 --> 00:19:23.863
Yes. I meant to keep it a secret

00:19:25.164 --> 00:19:26.165
but now you know.

00:19:29.602 --> 00:19:30.603
Are you okay?

00:19:31.337 --> 00:19:35.641
The training schedule is so intense.
You need to rest during breaks.

00:19:35.708 --> 00:19:38.244
I have no time to rest
because I'm not good enough.

00:19:46.552 --> 00:19:47.620
But...

00:19:50.222 --> 00:19:51.490
That's not all.

00:20:02.468 --> 00:20:05.938
I have a dream too.

00:20:07.473 --> 00:20:08.808
What is it?

00:20:09.742 --> 00:20:10.743
It's...

00:20:15.314 --> 00:20:16.348
Someday...

00:20:18.951 --> 00:20:20.686
I don't want to be known
as the brother of TORINNER's Ryo.

00:20:21.320 --> 00:20:22.822
I want to be recognized

00:20:24.623 --> 00:20:26.392
as NAZE's Yuya by other people.

00:20:28.561 --> 00:20:31.564
So for now, instead of worrying

00:20:32.798 --> 00:20:34.400
I just want to work hard.

00:20:48.881 --> 00:20:52.184
Yuya, there's something...

00:20:55.020 --> 00:20:56.756
I want to tell everyone.

00:20:57.790 --> 00:21:00.726
I haven't told you guys

00:21:01.427 --> 00:21:05.564
but I'm actually preparing
for your first live performance.

00:21:06.699 --> 00:21:08.067
Our first live performance...

00:21:08.134 --> 00:21:11.036
- Yay!
- Yay!

00:21:11.137 --> 00:21:12.872
When? Where will we do it?

00:21:12.972 --> 00:21:14.940
I can't tell you the details yet.

00:21:15.608 --> 00:21:20.946
- A live performance! Yay!
- Awesome!

00:21:21.013 --> 00:21:22.815
Minase, thank you so much!

00:21:23.415 --> 00:21:25.417
Now we will work even harder!

00:21:25.518 --> 00:21:28.854
- We'll do our best!
- We'll do our best!

00:21:30.890 --> 00:21:34.059
You sure about
making a promise like that?

00:21:34.894 --> 00:21:37.696
Did your best effort
produce results, ant girl?

00:21:39.832 --> 00:21:40.933
I'll do something.

00:21:42.968 --> 00:21:45.237
- I have a contact.
- Contact?

00:21:46.739 --> 00:21:49.975
I have a friend
who works at a record company.

00:21:50.876 --> 00:21:55.514
I'm sure she'll introduce me
to a business partner if I ask.

00:21:56.182 --> 00:21:57.383
A friend?

00:21:57.983 --> 00:21:59.118
From high school.

00:22:00.820 --> 00:22:01.821
She was my classmate.

00:22:06.158 --> 00:22:08.360
I heard the reason
you went to university in Korea

00:22:08.460 --> 00:22:11.230
was that you had
a hard time in high school.

00:22:14.633 --> 00:22:16.202
Well, that's in the past.

00:22:17.336 --> 00:22:21.140
We're both adults now.

00:22:24.109 --> 00:22:25.211
It's been a while. How are you?

00:22:25.277 --> 00:22:26.378
I'm sorry to contact you so suddenly

00:22:26.445 --> 00:22:27.546
But I'd like to see you
If you don't mind.

00:22:41.393 --> 00:22:43.662
I'm so excited!

00:22:43.762 --> 00:22:45.931
I can't believe we'll be able
to perform so soon!

00:22:46.398 --> 00:22:50.336
- That's so lit!
- So lit!

00:22:50.402 --> 00:22:52.037
Stop it...

00:22:52.137 --> 00:22:53.873
Mr. Azuma!

00:22:53.939 --> 00:22:55.140
Thank you!

00:22:55.207 --> 00:22:56.408
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

00:22:56.475 --> 00:22:59.111
I can't believe we're allowed
to perform already!

00:22:59.178 --> 00:23:01.347
Right? I had no idea either.

00:23:02.147 --> 00:23:03.682
What? Even you?

00:23:04.283 --> 00:23:07.519
Does that mean Minase has been
preparing it all by herself?

00:23:32.745 --> 00:23:33.812
Minase?

00:23:35.915 --> 00:23:39.518
Minase! I haven't seen you
for so long! Have you been well?

00:23:39.618 --> 00:23:42.521
Yes... I mean, yeah.

00:23:43.255 --> 00:23:44.356
All right!

00:23:45.491 --> 00:23:49.895
Wow, you're the manager
of a K-pop group? That's impressive.

00:23:50.596 --> 00:23:53.699
Not at all. Your career
is more impressive, Reina.

00:23:54.300 --> 00:23:57.136
You achieved your dream
of workingat a record company.

00:23:57.202 --> 00:23:59.605
No! I've been exaggerating.

00:23:59.939 --> 00:24:03.842
In reality, my stubborn boss
bosses me around every day.

00:24:05.444 --> 00:24:09.081
Well, Minase, you're admirable.
You traveled all the way to Korea.

00:24:09.181 --> 00:24:12.217
You're fighting with your own power.

00:24:16.355 --> 00:24:19.558
Reina, you've changed somehow.

00:24:23.562 --> 00:24:25.531
So...

00:24:26.131 --> 00:24:30.002
These are the artists
I'm in charge of.

00:24:30.069 --> 00:24:31.470
Wow, is that so?

00:24:32.538 --> 00:24:34.039
I see. So they're NAZE?

00:24:34.139 --> 00:24:38.477
They are very good boys.
They practice for 14 hours a day.

00:24:39.078 --> 00:24:41.080
They're diligent and work very hard.

00:24:42.548 --> 00:24:45.918
I've been searching for places
for them to hold a live performance

00:24:46.018 --> 00:24:47.519
but it's been difficult.

00:24:50.622 --> 00:24:52.758
Okay, I'll work things out.

00:24:53.959 --> 00:24:55.094
- Really?
- Yeah.

00:24:55.694 --> 00:24:57.997
There's a festival looking for

00:24:58.063 --> 00:24:59.331
a new boy group
with no experience to perform.

00:24:59.431 --> 00:25:02.401
- I'll ask.
- Wow, thank you!

00:25:02.768 --> 00:25:05.637
I'll also introduce you
to our partner companies.

00:25:05.738 --> 00:25:07.639
Can I take this?

00:25:07.740 --> 00:25:08.841
Of course!

00:25:09.575 --> 00:25:10.976
Thank you so much!

00:25:14.213 --> 00:25:16.515
I'm not doing this to make up
for what I did, but...

00:25:17.549 --> 00:25:19.284
- What?
- I mean, remember?

00:25:20.619 --> 00:25:23.455
Many things happened
between us, right?

00:25:25.424 --> 00:25:30.396
I thought
I needed to face you properly.

00:25:34.033 --> 00:25:35.634
I don't mind at all.

00:25:37.536 --> 00:25:38.604
I'm glad.

00:25:42.708 --> 00:25:45.444
- Wow!
- Wow!

00:25:45.744 --> 00:25:47.346
Is this the place?

00:25:49.581 --> 00:25:51.583
Members of NAZE, this way, please.

00:25:52.184 --> 00:25:54.486
- Yes! Pleased to work with you!
- Yes! Pleased to work with you!

00:25:55.087 --> 00:25:56.221
Likewise. This way, please.

00:25:57.122 --> 00:25:58.557
Let's go!

00:26:00.359 --> 00:26:02.461
Line up here for merch.

00:26:02.528 --> 00:26:04.630
Queue here for merch.

00:26:05.130 --> 00:26:07.666
We still have stock,
so there's no need to rush.

00:26:07.766 --> 00:26:08.901
One tote bag?

00:26:11.303 --> 00:26:14.073
- What's going on?
- I don't get it, either!

00:26:14.173 --> 00:26:15.641
Excuse me.

00:26:15.707 --> 00:26:19.545
You're here. You're late! I'm hungry.

00:26:19.645 --> 00:26:20.846
We'll get things ready at once.

00:26:21.914 --> 00:26:23.082
Wow, sushi!

00:26:23.916 --> 00:26:25.884
This is the end of the restroom line!

00:26:25.951 --> 00:26:28.720
Hey, why are there so few restrooms?

00:26:28.821 --> 00:26:30.689
Let us use the men's restroom!

00:26:30.756 --> 00:26:33.425
Minase, is this really our job?

00:26:33.492 --> 00:26:36.028
Sorry, my friend said
you should learn

00:26:36.095 --> 00:26:39.331
how to work backstage
at live shows first.

00:26:40.466 --> 00:26:43.235
- Are you kidding me?
- I'm sorry.

00:26:43.335 --> 00:26:45.871
We're commemorating the
40th anniversary of an enka singer.

00:26:45.971 --> 00:26:47.973
Would you like
to listen to some Enka?

00:26:48.073 --> 00:26:49.708
It's the 40th anniversary.

00:26:49.808 --> 00:26:51.009
Please take a look.

00:26:51.076 --> 00:26:55.114
Guys, will we really get to perform?

00:27:00.986 --> 00:27:04.456
Of course. I'll check just in case.

00:27:04.957 --> 00:27:07.459
ARAGAKI REINA

00:27:18.604 --> 00:27:19.605
Isn't this Mr. Azuma's book?

00:27:22.274 --> 00:27:23.509
BASIC VIDEO EDITING

00:27:25.077 --> 00:27:27.679
- You forgot this.
- Thanks.

00:27:29.948 --> 00:27:32.251
Why have you been reading that book?

00:27:36.355 --> 00:27:37.389
A career change?

00:27:39.658 --> 00:27:40.692
Wait, a career change?

00:27:40.792 --> 00:27:41.793
What?

00:27:42.127 --> 00:27:45.397
Are you planning
to change jobs and leave us?

00:27:47.032 --> 00:27:49.535
I mean, I don't want to be homeless.

00:27:49.601 --> 00:27:53.539
Wait! Aren't you going to take
responsibility for the boys' lives?

00:27:53.605 --> 00:27:55.107
- Are you running away?
- Calm down.

00:27:55.207 --> 00:27:58.710
I can't! The boys are working so hard

00:27:59.178 --> 00:28:02.114
but you've been playing around
in Shin-Okubo.

00:28:02.181 --> 00:28:03.615
And now you're job hunting?

00:28:04.216 --> 00:28:05.751
Don't be ridiculous!

00:28:11.723 --> 00:28:14.226
Her imagination
got the better of her again.

00:28:14.960 --> 00:28:16.862
So how is it going?

00:28:17.396 --> 00:28:20.098
Just leave it to me, CEO.

00:28:30.742 --> 00:28:33.245
Hey, Minase! What's the matter?

00:28:33.612 --> 00:28:35.147
What did you want to ask so urgently?

00:28:35.247 --> 00:28:36.848
Who is she?

00:28:38.450 --> 00:28:39.585
My best friend.

00:28:42.854 --> 00:28:44.156
So...

00:28:44.623 --> 00:28:48.026
When will you decide on
the dateof their live performance?

00:28:48.393 --> 00:28:49.661
- Come again.
- Of course...

00:28:50.128 --> 00:28:53.031
we'll continue to help
if it's necessary.

00:28:53.298 --> 00:28:57.436
But I thought having a goal
might boost their motivation.

00:29:00.372 --> 00:29:01.406
Reina?

00:29:05.244 --> 00:29:06.745
Seriously? Are you stupid?

00:29:07.512 --> 00:29:09.514
It was a lie, of course!

00:29:09.581 --> 00:29:11.416
What would I stand to gain

00:29:11.516 --> 00:29:15.187
from having such amateurs
perform at our live show?

00:29:17.022 --> 00:29:21.393
This girl has always been
a goody-two-shoes.

00:29:21.460 --> 00:29:22.961
- Wow.
- Is she?

00:29:23.028 --> 00:29:24.496
She does look serious to a fault.

00:29:24.563 --> 00:29:28.166
I'm so glad
that you haven't changed at all.

00:29:30.002 --> 00:29:33.238
Okay. Let's stop talking about work
and have some fun.

00:29:33.605 --> 00:29:35.107
Join us, Minase!

00:29:35.173 --> 00:29:37.542
Yes, have a drink with us!

00:29:37.609 --> 00:29:40.279
If you aren't prepared
to be responsible for their lives

00:29:40.379 --> 00:29:42.180
our team doesn't need you.

00:29:43.115 --> 00:29:45.017
- Drink!
- Come here.

00:29:45.083 --> 00:29:47.586
Come and have a drink with us!

00:29:48.120 --> 00:29:49.388
Hello?

00:29:51.890 --> 00:29:53.191
Please!

00:29:54.226 --> 00:29:58.163
Please let them perform.

00:29:58.764 --> 00:30:01.133
The boys are still inexperienced.

00:30:01.667 --> 00:30:04.102
But they're working hard every day

00:30:04.169 --> 00:30:06.438
and they believe
that it will come true.

00:30:07.472 --> 00:30:10.075
Of course, hard work is a given.

00:30:12.010 --> 00:30:13.111
But...

00:30:15.180 --> 00:30:16.481
Even for a short while...

00:30:17.916 --> 00:30:19.718
If you could see them for just a bit

00:30:20.085 --> 00:30:24.423
you'll know how hard they are trying.

00:30:27.125 --> 00:30:31.029
Please spare me
a little of your time.

00:30:33.098 --> 00:30:34.166
Please...

00:30:36.902 --> 00:30:38.136
Please help me!

00:30:42.174 --> 00:30:44.609
You're so full of yourself

00:30:44.676 --> 00:30:46.678
just because young,handsome men
rely on you.

00:30:48.447 --> 00:30:49.815
Don't get cocky.

00:30:53.919 --> 00:30:55.954
You've always been a loser.

00:30:59.624 --> 00:31:01.026
Poor thing!

00:31:01.093 --> 00:31:03.495
Don't waste food!

00:31:03.562 --> 00:31:04.930
What's wrong, Minase?

00:31:05.330 --> 00:31:07.165
- What?
- Minase?

00:31:07.799 --> 00:31:08.900
Why?

00:31:11.336 --> 00:31:12.371
I'm sorry.

00:31:12.804 --> 00:31:13.805
The live performance...

00:31:15.707 --> 00:31:16.708
It fell through.

00:31:17.275 --> 00:31:18.276
What?

00:31:18.510 --> 00:31:20.278
It's my fault.

00:31:21.713 --> 00:31:22.748
I'm sorry.

00:31:30.689 --> 00:31:32.691
You look pretty depressed.

00:31:33.291 --> 00:31:34.559
Let's cheer up!

00:31:36.061 --> 00:31:38.163
Hey, full-power ant girl.

00:31:39.164 --> 00:31:40.265
What's with the camera?

00:31:42.167 --> 00:31:43.235
I...

00:31:45.737 --> 00:31:46.872
I'm sorry.

00:31:50.709 --> 00:31:52.544
The live performance fell through.

00:31:53.779 --> 00:31:55.247
Is that so?

00:31:55.380 --> 00:31:56.915
I said I had the resolve

00:31:57.849 --> 00:31:59.251
but in the end,
I relied on someone else

00:31:59.985 --> 00:32:01.386
and caused trouble for everyone.

00:32:01.920 --> 00:32:04.990
I couldn't be of any help.

00:32:07.292 --> 00:32:08.660
I...

00:32:13.398 --> 00:32:15.534
Who decided you weren't useful?

00:32:16.935 --> 00:32:18.036
What?

00:32:24.009 --> 00:32:25.243
Testing...

00:32:25.310 --> 00:32:27.679
What is this place?

00:32:27.746 --> 00:32:29.915
Testing...

00:32:30.916 --> 00:32:32.317
Check the camera on the stage...

00:32:32.417 --> 00:32:33.985
STAFF ENTRANCE

00:32:35.153 --> 00:32:36.788
Excuse me, what are we doing here?

00:32:37.389 --> 00:32:39.891
Waiting for the event organizer
and Mynavi.

00:32:41.326 --> 00:32:42.427
Do you mean
that human resources company?

00:32:42.527 --> 00:32:45.730
Yes, and the main sponsor of TGC.

00:32:46.431 --> 00:32:47.966
TGC?

00:32:48.066 --> 00:32:49.634
The one we saw in the advert?

00:32:49.734 --> 00:32:52.871
Yes. Tokyo Girls Collection.

00:32:52.971 --> 00:32:55.106
The fashion event is very popular

00:32:55.207 --> 00:32:56.875
among girls in their teens
and their twenties.

00:32:58.977 --> 00:33:01.847
- Ms. Yamane and Mr. Sakai. This way.
- Hello, Mr. Azuma.

00:33:01.947 --> 00:33:03.114
Nice to meet you.

00:33:03.582 --> 00:33:04.883
Nice to meet you.

00:33:04.950 --> 00:33:08.053
I'm Sakai,
the casting director for TGC.

00:33:08.153 --> 00:33:09.454
Thank you.

00:33:10.021 --> 00:33:11.756
This is Ms. Yamane,
the PR Department Head.

00:33:11.857 --> 00:33:14.326
- Nice to meet you.
- And our PR Team.

00:33:14.426 --> 00:33:15.760
Nice to meet you.

00:33:15.827 --> 00:33:18.363
Thank you for your time today.

00:33:18.864 --> 00:33:22.167
The video I mentioned the other day
is ready. Would you like to watch it?

00:33:22.434 --> 00:33:25.270
It will be streamed in Japan,
Korea, and Thailand at 7 p.m.

00:33:25.370 --> 00:33:26.605
Let's watch it.

00:33:26.705 --> 00:33:28.206
Video?

00:33:28.507 --> 00:33:29.875
No idea.

00:33:29.975 --> 00:33:32.811
I'll play it now.

00:33:35.247 --> 00:33:36.548
NAZE CHANNEL

00:33:36.615 --> 00:33:37.716
- What's that?
- What's that?

00:33:37.782 --> 00:33:38.783
- Video?
- What?

00:33:38.884 --> 00:33:40.118
Sixty-one.

00:33:40.218 --> 00:33:41.453
I'm turning on the washing machine!

00:33:41.553 --> 00:33:43.421
A DOCUMENTARY ON NAZE,
A NEW K-POP GROUP

00:33:44.923 --> 00:33:46.224
When was this filmed?

00:33:46.324 --> 00:33:47.392
You secretly filmed us!

00:33:49.928 --> 00:33:52.430
- Guys, hang in there!
- Do your best!

00:33:52.497 --> 00:33:54.165
Yuya, let's go!

00:33:54.266 --> 00:33:55.400
I can't believe this!

00:33:57.869 --> 00:33:59.104
Hey, wait!

00:33:59.170 --> 00:34:02.674
KAISEI AND TURN ARE PANICKING

00:34:02.774 --> 00:34:04.809
Oh, my... Oh, my God!

00:34:07.112 --> 00:34:09.648
Please. Yes, thank you!

00:34:09.714 --> 00:34:10.782
SOLD

00:34:10.849 --> 00:34:12.517
Hey, the change! The change!

00:34:12.584 --> 00:34:16.187
Don't just apologize!
Tell me how long the wait is!

00:34:16.254 --> 00:34:17.622
THE LINE FOR THE WOMEN'S RESTROOM

00:34:18.657 --> 00:34:20.292
My god, I'm so embarrassed!

00:34:20.392 --> 00:34:21.493
COUNTDOWN UNTIL TRAGEDY

00:34:27.532 --> 00:34:28.567
What do you think?

00:34:29.301 --> 00:34:32.037
They're as clumsy
as I told you, right?

00:34:32.137 --> 00:34:34.606
Indeed, they're pretty clumsy.

00:34:45.083 --> 00:34:47.419
It's true that they're clumsy

00:34:48.086 --> 00:34:51.489
but they are working very hard.

00:34:52.223 --> 00:34:55.760
They believe in their dreams,
and their hard work is real.

00:35:02.067 --> 00:35:03.068
I am very sorry.

00:35:10.542 --> 00:35:11.810
Please!

00:35:12.477 --> 00:35:13.912
Please...

00:35:14.012 --> 00:35:15.914
let them perform.

00:35:16.514 --> 00:35:18.316
- Don't get cocky.
- You even filmed this?

00:35:18.416 --> 00:35:20.485
You've always been a loser.

00:35:24.255 --> 00:35:25.323
So nasty!

00:35:25.924 --> 00:35:28.727
- Please...
- Just leave, for goodness' sake.

00:35:33.498 --> 00:35:36.601
Please...

00:35:37.202 --> 00:35:38.503
Please!

00:35:39.504 --> 00:35:40.905
Please!

00:35:40.972 --> 00:35:42.273
Leave!

00:35:43.842 --> 00:35:45.510
The members are clumsy

00:35:46.311 --> 00:35:47.879
and the same goes for the manager.

00:35:48.613 --> 00:35:50.949
No, she's even clumsier.

00:35:51.716 --> 00:35:53.284
What a headache.

00:35:54.219 --> 00:35:58.223
But when the members see
how hard she is trying

00:35:58.690 --> 00:36:00.759
they also give it their all.

00:36:01.359 --> 00:36:04.462
When she sees how hard they work,
she works even harder.

00:36:05.597 --> 00:36:09.934
And the members work even harder,
as if in response to her efforts.

00:36:11.169 --> 00:36:12.971
To achieve their dreams

00:36:14.439 --> 00:36:16.107
they support each other
with all their might.

00:36:17.509 --> 00:36:21.613
Their ways may be
unsophisticated and outdated now

00:36:22.213 --> 00:36:26.217
But that's what our team is proud of.

00:36:35.894 --> 00:36:38.430
Ms. Yamane, what do you think?

00:36:41.032 --> 00:36:42.834
They showed us something good.

00:36:44.803 --> 00:36:46.037
Thank you.

00:36:48.873 --> 00:36:52.744
The way you pursue
your dreams with unwavering resolve

00:36:53.378 --> 00:36:56.514
will surely give courage
to the younger generation.

00:36:57.015 --> 00:37:02.387
I've fully felt NAZE's unique charm.

00:37:05.924 --> 00:37:10.095
May I confirm Naze's appearance
at TGC, then?

00:37:10.161 --> 00:37:11.629
- What?
- Appearance?

00:37:15.834 --> 00:37:16.835
Of course.

00:37:17.435 --> 00:37:20.438
We look forward to an unsophisticated
yet amazing performance.

00:37:21.039 --> 00:37:22.407
TGC...

00:37:23.074 --> 00:37:25.977
- TGC!
- Yay!

00:37:30.181 --> 00:37:31.316
Minase!

00:37:32.450 --> 00:37:33.651
It's all thanks to you.

00:37:34.619 --> 00:37:37.689
We promise we'll make this
a great performance.

00:37:41.059 --> 00:37:42.093
Okay.

00:37:46.397 --> 00:37:48.433
- Minase...
- Minase...

00:37:51.002 --> 00:37:53.538
- Minase...
- Minase...

00:37:54.105 --> 00:37:57.976
Come on, stop crying.

00:38:21.900 --> 00:38:23.568
- Let's go!
- Go!

00:38:24.169 --> 00:38:25.537
One, two, three.

00:38:26.204 --> 00:38:27.605
NAZE!

00:38:31.409 --> 00:38:35.780
Next up, we have a rookie group
that we added at the last minute.

00:38:35.847 --> 00:38:37.415
Please welcome NAZE!

00:38:39.117 --> 00:38:41.152
- Who?
- No idea. Haven't seen them before.

00:38:41.252 --> 00:38:42.554
They're from the video yesterday....

00:38:42.620 --> 00:38:44.189
The one from
that hidden camera video...

00:38:45.757 --> 00:38:47.725
- Saw them on social media.
- K-pop again?

00:39:21.659 --> 00:39:23.494
I like how that blond guy dances.

00:39:24.796 --> 00:39:26.898
They look so innocent
and cute. I can't look away!

00:40:08.640 --> 00:40:09.874
Amazing!

00:40:10.308 --> 00:40:12.677
It all went according
to Azuma's plan.

00:40:13.811 --> 00:40:15.513
- What?
- Our agency is poor.

00:40:16.114 --> 00:40:18.917
There's no way we could
place big ads like TORINNER.

00:40:19.884 --> 00:40:21.619
So you chose TGC?

00:40:21.686 --> 00:40:22.687
Yes.

00:40:22.921 --> 00:40:27.191
That was when we decided
to make a promotional video.

00:40:27.292 --> 00:40:30.361
We researched
what kind of videos young girls like.

00:40:30.461 --> 00:40:34.766
We had no money to outsource,
so Azuma learned how to edit videos.

00:40:35.166 --> 00:40:37.468
It was quite touching!

00:40:37.535 --> 00:40:40.138
The old guy pulled all-nighters
to work on it!

00:40:42.807 --> 00:40:44.809
So you've been working hard.

00:40:45.310 --> 00:40:49.047
I had no idea
and was rude to you. I'm sorry.

00:40:49.447 --> 00:40:50.715
It's no big deal.

00:40:51.049 --> 00:40:52.317
After all

00:40:52.817 --> 00:40:54.485
I only realized that

00:40:54.986 --> 00:40:57.655
their biggest selling point
is their grit and determination

00:40:58.589 --> 00:40:59.824
because of this.

00:41:00.725 --> 00:41:02.493
You read it?

00:41:03.061 --> 00:41:04.796
They're not working smart at all

00:41:05.196 --> 00:41:07.365
but they're sincerely working hard
towards their dreams.

00:41:07.465 --> 00:41:09.267
So I thought showing
their daily lives as they are

00:41:09.334 --> 00:41:11.302
would be the best way
to attract people.

00:41:12.503 --> 00:41:15.807
This is way too detailed, though.
You're almost like a stalker.

00:41:16.274 --> 00:41:18.076
That's uncalled for!

00:41:18.676 --> 00:41:21.946
Isn't there something else
you should say to Minase?

00:41:26.784 --> 00:41:27.852
Well...

00:41:30.421 --> 00:41:31.556
You are...

00:41:33.391 --> 00:41:34.392
an ant.

00:41:35.259 --> 00:41:36.260
Yes.

00:41:36.327 --> 00:41:37.395
Ants are tiny.

00:41:37.929 --> 00:41:40.398
A tiny creature
that only crawls on the ground.

00:41:40.465 --> 00:41:42.033
Not fascinating at all.

00:41:42.767 --> 00:41:43.935
But do you know?

00:41:45.470 --> 00:41:47.038
Ants are incredibly strong.

00:41:47.505 --> 00:41:51.175
They can lift 50 times
their own body weight.

00:41:54.612 --> 00:41:56.014
Our work requires us

00:41:57.815 --> 00:42:00.084
to bear the burden of others' lives.

00:42:01.486 --> 00:42:04.756
Of course, that requires
a sense of responsibility

00:42:05.323 --> 00:42:07.191
and a vision for the future.

00:42:08.726 --> 00:42:10.261
But more than that

00:42:11.863 --> 00:42:14.399
you need to be ableto support

00:42:15.566 --> 00:42:17.435
and lift others with sincere effort.

00:42:19.270 --> 00:42:20.271
Just like what you're doing.

00:42:24.709 --> 00:42:25.877
Our team...

00:42:27.745 --> 00:42:29.080
needs you, Endo Minase.

00:42:33.584 --> 00:42:34.685
I'll be counting on you.

00:42:44.195 --> 00:42:45.263
I'm happy.

00:42:46.898 --> 00:42:48.132
I'm happy.

00:42:48.933 --> 00:42:51.369
- You said my name.
- That's what you're happy about?

00:42:53.638 --> 00:42:58.709
I'm going to give it my all
to lift them up!

00:43:01.813 --> 00:43:02.914
Okay.

00:43:12.590 --> 00:43:15.893
The group produced by Azuma
is being featured in many articles.

00:43:15.993 --> 00:43:17.728
Please don't worry.

00:43:18.096 --> 00:43:20.498
I'll destroy them as you instructed.

00:43:21.099 --> 00:43:23.034
I can't let

00:43:23.734 --> 00:43:25.103
that murderer walk free.

00:43:28.306 --> 00:43:29.607
I'm counting on you

00:43:30.408 --> 00:43:31.509
Ms. Park.

00:43:32.610 --> 00:43:33.945
This is bad!

00:43:34.479 --> 00:43:35.646
Park Ji-soo...

00:43:36.214 --> 00:43:37.315
TORINNER...

00:43:38.216 --> 00:43:40.218
They're going
to be promoting in Japan!

00:43:43.921 --> 00:43:46.390
Looks, style... Defeated in all.

00:43:46.491 --> 00:43:48.059
NAZE is just our group's leftovers.

00:43:48.159 --> 00:43:49.894
Once they step on the stage,
it's the end for them.

00:43:49.994 --> 00:43:51.129
Will you perform
at our live performance?

00:43:51.195 --> 00:43:53.764
- Put on a show that only we can do.
- Yes!

00:43:53.865 --> 00:43:55.099
This is where it begins.

00:43:55.199 --> 00:43:57.735
I won't forgive anyone
who makes a fool of my friends.

00:43:57.835 --> 00:43:58.870
I'll knock you out
if you do it again.